1
00:00:10,467 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>Take me back to the Philippines!</i>

2
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:18,267
<i>You all behave, especially you.</i>

3
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,500
<i> How did you get a cell phone?</i>

4
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> I got it from the guard.</i>

5
00:00:20,867 --> 00:00:22,700
<i>Miss, do you know anyone
we can call?</i>

6
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,000
<i>Anyone that we can ask for help?</i>

7
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,200
<i>Ma'am Bobby,
I'm with your godsister.</i>

8
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:28,333
<i>They're taking us to Milan,
to Duomo.</i>

9
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:29,733
<i> Conde, Garcia, and Enriquez,</i>

10
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:30,800
<i>bring Selena
and the others home.</i>

11
00:00:30,933 --> 00:00:32,467
<i>- Go to Milan.
- Yes, Sir.</i>

12
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> This means,</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>we won't have any more problems
with Selena.</i>

14
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:37,900
<i>Ready to be sold
to the highest bidder.</i>

15
00:00:38,033 --> 00:00:39,267
<i>You won't have
a headache anymore,</i>

16
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:40,233
<i> and you earned a lot, too.</i>

17
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:41,600
<i> It's nice here in Milan, Sir.</i>

18
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:42,700
<i> It's just ironic.</i>

19
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,500
<i>This Cathedral is very peaceful,</i>

20
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:46,367
<i>but what we are looking
for are demons.</i>

21
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:48,467
<i>Get ready. Later,
we will go to the event.</i>

22
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,233
<i>Follow all our orders,
so that no one gets hurt,</i>

23
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:52,200
<i> especially you.</i>

24
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,000
<i>I will make sure
to dispatch you.</i>

25
00:00:54,133 --> 00:00:55,533
<i>- I saw him.
- Are you sure?</i>

26
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:56,600
<i> I'm positive, it's Markus.</i>

27
00:00:56,733 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>And now, let's bring
in girl number 19.</i>

28
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,167
<i> You may scan the QR code.</i>

29
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,667
<i> 45 for bidder number 10!</i>

30
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:05,367
<i>75,000 US dollars
for bidder number 6.</i>

31
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,467
<i> Going once...</i>

32
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,600
<i> Going twice...</i>

33
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:09,467
<i> Sold to bidder number 6!</i>

34
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,500
<i>I'll follow him. I will send you
the location.</i>

35
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:12,833
<i> They are still here.</i>

36
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:33,900
Relax.

37
00:01:34,033 --> 00:01:36,100
I'm going to take care of you.

38
00:01:43,233 --> 00:01:45,067
Stop the car now!

39
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,667
Sis, my beauty is gone.

40
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:26,900
Oh, what beauty?

41
00:02:27,033 --> 00:02:28,000
You don't have it.

42
00:02:28,133 --> 00:02:29,333
Girl, you don't have it.

43
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:31,033
Haggard, yes.

44
00:02:31,167 --> 00:02:33,567
You know, Abdul, we're so tired.

45
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,333
While, one of us is not helping.

46
00:02:35,467 --> 00:02:36,500
She's just using her cell phone,

47
00:02:36,633 --> 00:02:37,800
- right?
- You're right.

48
00:02:37,933 --> 00:02:39,067
Who? Me?

49
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,433
Oh, no, Captain.

50
00:02:40,567 --> 00:02:42,400
-It's tiring to use a cellphone.
-Bobby texted.

51
00:02:42,533 --> 00:02:44,500
Oh, Bobby texted?

52
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:47,233
- What's the latest, Captain?
- Can I see?

53
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,967
Oh! She's really something else,
girl!

54
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:53,567
From Dubai to Milan,

55
00:02:53,700 --> 00:02:56,833
Italy, the fashion capital
of the world.

56
00:02:56,967 --> 00:02:58,167
Italy?

57
00:02:58,300 --> 00:03:00,200
Do you want me to tie you up?

58
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,333
That's Paris!

59
00:03:01,467 --> 00:03:03,600
Fashion capital of the world.

60
00:03:03,733 --> 00:03:05,933
You know, Abdul, you don't have
a sense of fashion.

61
00:03:06,067 --> 00:03:07,333
You don't know the big four?

62
00:03:07,467 --> 00:03:09,767
- What's that? Go.
- Big four...

63
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:13,267
Paris, Milan, London,
and New York.

64
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,467
Oh, see?

65
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,833
You thought you knew
a lot about fashion.

66
00:03:16,967 --> 00:03:18,533
- Oh!
- You don't know how to catwalk.

67
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:19,800
Oh, really?

68
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,833
- Oh, okay, go!
- Okay!

69
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:24,433
- Captain, Abdul, move aside.
- Okay.

70
00:03:24,567 --> 00:03:26,433
- Ladies and gentlemen...
- Okay.

71
00:03:26,567 --> 00:03:29,333
Marcy from...

72
00:03:29,467 --> 00:03:30,900
Chile!

73
00:03:31,033 --> 00:03:32,267
A round of aplause, please?

74
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,500
That's a majorette?

75
00:03:33,633 --> 00:03:34,967
Oh, okay.

76
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:38,200
And you really blew fire.

77
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,200
You're so shameless.

78
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,100
- Okay.
- Excuse me.

79
00:03:42,967 --> 00:03:44,600
Oh...

80
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:48,367
Can you do that?

81
00:03:50,533 --> 00:03:52,300
Thank you, thank you!

82
00:03:52,433 --> 00:03:53,767
Mar, step aside. Okay?

83
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,500
-You really thought so.
-A round of applause, everyone?

84
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:56,700
Okay.

85
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,133
So cheap, my God.

86
00:03:58,267 --> 00:04:02,000
Ladies and gentlemen,
Abdul, Philippines.

87
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:04,100
The one and only goddess
of beauty.

88
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:06,667
So cheap!

89
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:09,167
This is how the winners
of the Miss Universe walk.

90
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:11,233
Looks like the Statue of Liberty
with a beard!

91
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:14,467
So cheap!

92
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,033
- You're like my father.
- Thank you, everyone!

93
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,133
- What? Still have an entry?
- It doesn't suit you.

94
00:04:22,267 --> 00:04:23,467
It doesn't suit you, girl!

95
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,533
You know what, let's find out
the result.

96
00:04:24,667 --> 00:04:26,200
Oh, let's go, let's go.

97
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:27,400
- Come, come, come.
- Stay here.

98
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,100
All right.

99
00:04:28,233 --> 00:04:30,100
Okay, Captain, tell us.

100
00:04:30,233 --> 00:04:31,233
Who's the winner?

101
00:04:31,367 --> 00:04:32,300
Is it Mar?

102
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:33,567
Is it Abdul?

103
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:36,400
Come on!

104
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:38,667
My town guards
are driving me crazy.

105
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,333
Captain, Captain!

106
00:04:41,667 --> 00:04:45,333
Wendy is raging over there,
fighting with Jay.

107
00:04:45,467 --> 00:04:46,667
- Let's go.
- Come on, let's go there.

108
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:48,967
- Let's go, let's go.
- Oh, slowly.

109
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,500
Let's go.

110
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:59,033
Bok, I'm sure they're inside.

111
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:01,100
Sir, let's go inside.

112
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:04,333
- Hey, hey, Enriquez!
- Enriquez, what's with you?

113
00:05:04,467 --> 00:05:05,967
We're not yet familiar
with what's inside.

114
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,300
We need to study that first.

115
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:16,767
Sir Tonyo...

116
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:23,900
You're useless!

117
00:05:24,033 --> 00:05:25,667
I really don't need you
in my life!

118
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,600
- What's that again?
- Hey, hey!

119
00:05:27,733 --> 00:05:29,133
- What are you fighting about?
- Oh, no.

120
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,333
We're just talking, Captain.

121
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:31,000
- Just talking?
- Yes.

122
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:32,167
You're choking your wife.

123
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:33,300
That's not true. Right, Love?

124
00:05:33,433 --> 00:05:35,300
Oh, the thing is, Captain...

125
00:05:35,467 --> 00:05:37,067
- Love!
- Stop it!

126
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,433
The thing is, Captain,

127
00:05:38,567 --> 00:05:40,067
this good-for-nothing
husband of mine,

128
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:44,067
he's just squandering the money
I sent to him on his friends!

129
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,600
Are you an OFW, Ma'am?

130
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:48,100
Yes. I worked there
for several years.

131
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:51,567
I thought we could build
our own house.

132
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:54,567
But what? This worthless man
didn't put up anything,

133
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:56,233
he didn't save anything!

134
00:05:56,367 --> 00:05:57,500
You animal!

135
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:59,267
And not only that...

136
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,633
he didn't even pick me up
at the airport

137
00:06:01,767 --> 00:06:03,867
because he's drinking!

138
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,033
- I'm just going to finish it!
- What?

139
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:07,133
You're so shameless!

140
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:08,600
Wait a minute.

141
00:06:08,733 --> 00:06:11,133
Is what she said true?

142
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:12,833
Yes, Sir.

143
00:06:12,967 --> 00:06:14,600
- Oh, take that!
- Ouch, Love!

144
00:06:14,733 --> 00:06:16,767
- You don't that to a woman!
- Ouch!

145
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:18,000
Okay? You don't do that.

146
00:06:18,133 --> 00:06:19,333
Maybe you're womanizing?

147
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:21,467
What? Love, I can't do that!

148
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:24,000
Okay, I admit it.
I was busy with my friends.

149
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:25,667
We drink here and there,

150
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,100
and gamble here and there.

151
00:06:27,233 --> 00:06:28,867
So, Love, I didn't notice
that...

152
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,367
the money you were sending me
is all gone.

153
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,033
- Forgive me.
- You're useless!

154
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:33,333
- You're annoying!
- Ouch, ouch!

155
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:34,667
You're a monster!

156
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,833
There's so much
I want to tell you,

157
00:06:36,967 --> 00:06:39,167
but I don't know where to start.

158
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:40,367
Captain, let me.

159
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:44,033
Priority, that's hard to learn.

160
00:06:44,167 --> 00:06:47,933
But you need to prioritize
your family, especially if...

161
00:06:48,067 --> 00:06:50,300
If you have something
you're saving up for!

162
00:06:50,433 --> 00:06:53,700
Your wife works,
and you're just like that?

163
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:56,033
A man should be the one
who stretches his bones.

164
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,667
- I'll hit you!
- No!

165
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,733
Do you want that?

166
00:06:58,867 --> 00:06:59,767
Stop me, Mar!

167
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:00,867
I'll hit this guy!

168
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,567
Besides, those friends,

169
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,267
alcohol, and gambling
won't do you any good.

170
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:06,900
Focus on your family,

171
00:07:07,033 --> 00:07:10,100
especially your wife,
who's struggling to work abroad!

172
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:11,233
I'll hit you!

173
00:07:11,367 --> 00:07:12,800
Love, stop them, Love.

174
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:14,367
Come on, come on!

175
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:16,267
Captain, maybe you want
to add something?

176
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,367
Yes!

177
00:07:17,500 --> 00:07:18,500
What else can I say?

178
00:07:18,633 --> 00:07:20,000
You've said it all.

179
00:07:20,133 --> 00:07:21,367
But remember this...

180
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:23,733
if you do that again,

181
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:25,733
I'll put you in jail!

182
00:07:25,867 --> 00:07:27,500
- There, that's right.
- That's right.

183
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:28,567
- Promise...
- Yes.

184
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:30,067
I'll make it up to you.

185
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,067
I'll work for us.

186
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:32,233
You just stay home.

187
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:34,233
I'll do everything
to make our lives better,

188
00:07:34,367 --> 00:07:36,200
to get back the money
I've wasted.

189
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:38,200
Love, thank you.

190
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,333
Oh my, Love.

191
00:07:39,467 --> 00:07:40,433
Oh my, you stink!

192
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:41,633
You smell like alcohol!

193
00:07:41,767 --> 00:07:43,467
Go take a shower first!

194
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:51,333
What are you doing here?

195
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:55,700
They sold me, but I escaped.

196
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,667
Selena...

197
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,000
have you seen Reign inside?

198
00:08:01,133 --> 00:08:02,067
Reign...

199
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:05,167
she's inside, but...

200
00:08:05,300 --> 00:08:08,100
but she might be the next one
to be sold at the auction.

201
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:09,367
What?

202
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,633
Auction?

203
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:13,300
I need to go inside.

204
00:08:13,433 --> 00:08:15,000
- Enriquez, what's with you?
- Ma'am Bobby, Ma'am Bobby!

205
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:16,167
Don't go in.

206
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:17,200
There are many guards inside.

207
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:18,467
If you come in now,

208
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,200
we'll all be in trouble.

209
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,033
But I need to save
my godsister.

210
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:25,233
We can't risk getting
all of us caught.

211
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:27,800
We may not be able
to save Reign.

212
00:08:27,933 --> 00:08:29,367
That's right, Enriquez.

213
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:32,067
Let's take Selena
to the safehouse first.

214
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,300
Let's secure her there first,

215
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:36,533
then we'll plan
how to save your godsister.

216
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:37,600
Let's go!

217
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:39,500
Let's go.

218
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:41,400
Let's go!

219
00:08:50,933 --> 00:08:52,833
Markus, Selena escaped.

220
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:55,300
-What?
-The buyer wants the money back.

221
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:01,567
She shouldn't return
to the Philippines.

222
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:11,800
- Here, Bok, coffee first.
- Thank you.

223
00:09:12,467 --> 00:09:14,533
Sir, I'll just take this
to Selena.

224
00:09:14,667 --> 00:09:15,733
Okay.

225
00:09:15,867 --> 00:09:18,133
Try asking her about Markus,
too.

226
00:09:18,267 --> 00:09:19,767
Okay.

227
00:09:21,067 --> 00:09:22,267
Bok...

228
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,900
What?

229
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:25,567
Call Chief.

230
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:28,967
Tell him we have Selena
in our hands.

231
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:34,300
But tell him that we saved her,
so we look good.

232
00:09:45,833 --> 00:09:47,400
Oh, Bok...

233
00:09:47,533 --> 00:09:49,567
why does it seem that you don't
want to call the Chief?

234
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:56,033
Because if he finds out...

235
00:09:56,167 --> 00:09:58,533
that we got Selena,

236
00:09:58,667 --> 00:10:00,467
he'll definitely send us home.

237
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:05,067
Even if we haven't saved
Enriquez's godsister yet?

238
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:08,400
Bok, you talk
to the Chief first.

239
00:10:08,533 --> 00:10:10,600
I'll talk to Selena too.

240
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:14,867
Maybe she knows how we can save
Enriquez's godsister.

241
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,900
Okay, okay,
I'll take care of it.

242
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:19,200
Okay.

243
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:27,633
Conde and Enriquez are really
something else, aren't they?

244
00:10:27,767 --> 00:10:28,800
Think about it.

245
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:31,233
The syndicate
took Selena abroad,

246
00:10:31,367 --> 00:10:33,000
but they still saved her.

247
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,400
And that's not all.

248
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:37,533
They still haven't stopped
rescuing the other girls too.

249
00:10:37,667 --> 00:10:40,200
You know, Dizon, you're so
impressed with them.

250
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:42,067
Haven't you heard Chief's story?

251
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,567
Selena escaped alone.

252
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:48,000
They just happened to be there
when Selena came out.

253
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:51,367
Is that your definition
of coincidence?

254
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:54,700
Do you think Conde wouldn't
have gotten to that point

255
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:57,033
if he hadn't worked
on his leads?

256
00:10:57,167 --> 00:10:59,600
And to think,
this is in a foreign country.

257
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:02,167
Well, it's just inspiring,
you know?

258
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:05,500
It feels like you want
to work harder at your job.

259
00:11:05,633 --> 00:11:07,067
Sir! Sir!

260
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,000
Wait, wait.
What's the problem?

261
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:11,067
We were going
to ask for help, Sir.

262
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:13,433
Oh, don't tell us your bra
was stolen again.

263
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:14,867
Maybe it's different this time,

264
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,067
maybe it's panties.

265
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,567
Hey, you two, stop it.

266
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:19,733
What happened?

267
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:23,267
A friend of ours,
we're worried about her.

268
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:25,833
She didn't make it
to our meeting place.

269
00:11:25,967 --> 00:11:27,133
She can't be contacted either.

270
00:11:27,267 --> 00:11:28,700
She's not like that.

271
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:29,733
That's why we're worried.

272
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:32,433
Maybe something bad happened
to her.

273
00:11:32,567 --> 00:11:34,867
When was the last time
you talked to Cherry?

274
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,067
Oh, in the afternoon, Sir.

275
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,333
Yes.

276
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:41,767
The last update she gave us
was that she was booking a ride.

277
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:44,200
Could this be connected to the
human trafficking syndicate

278
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,267
that Conde is investigating?

279
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,800
Dizon, you're overreacting.

280
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:49,033
It's not connected to that.

281
00:11:49,167 --> 00:11:51,833
We haven't gotten any leads yet.

282
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,700
The incidents are happening
one after another,

283
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,400
which is why you can't help
but think.

284
00:11:55,533 --> 00:11:56,733
Our point is,

285
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:59,633
don't worry too much
about your friend.

286
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:01,833
Many things could happen.

287
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,633
Maybe your friend just wants
to stood you up?

288
00:12:05,767 --> 00:12:09,267
Oh, Sir, our friend
is not like that.

289
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:12,567
Don't worry, we will help you.

290
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:14,867
Dizon, you won't get anything
from these people.

291
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:17,333
You're just wasting time...

292
00:12:17,467 --> 00:12:19,567
unless you like them both.

293
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:23,800
Bro, this is just work.

294
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:27,633
What other details
can you give us?

295
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:30,367
Oh, I can't think
of anything, Apple.

296
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:33,033
This is hard,
harder than Math.

297
00:12:33,167 --> 00:12:35,733
Didn't you say earlier
that she booked a ride?

298
00:12:35,867 --> 00:12:38,233
Do you know where her pick-up
point usually is?

299
00:12:39,733 --> 00:12:40,833
Yes.

300
00:12:51,767 --> 00:12:55,433
Enriquez, Garcia is already
talking to the Chief.

301
00:12:55,567 --> 00:12:58,467
Selena, do you know
where Reign is?

302
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:01,200
Didn't you mention in your text
that you two were together?

303
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:02,700
Do you know where she was taken?

304
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:03,867
I'm sorry, Ma'am Bobby.

305
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,900
I really don't know
where they would sell her.

306
00:13:07,033 --> 00:13:07,933
I need to go back to get Reign.

307
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:09,367
Bobby...

308
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,433
it's dangerous.

309
00:13:11,567 --> 00:13:14,067
Reign will be in more danger
if we rush there now.

310
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,367
Tomorrow...

311
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:20,533
we'll come back.

312
00:13:21,567 --> 00:13:24,033
We'll save your godsister.

313
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,300
Selena...

314
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:32,567
can you tell us
what to expect inside?

315
00:13:33,367 --> 00:13:34,500
Okay.

316
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,867
Yes, okay.

317
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,767
Thanks for calling, Bobby.

318
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,433
Take care.

319
00:13:44,567 --> 00:13:46,633
-Bye.
-Don't forget our tokens, Bobby!

320
00:13:46,767 --> 00:13:47,633
She's gone.

321
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:48,967
All you think about is tokens.

322
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,867
You know that she's busy.

323
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,933
I know that, Abdul.

324
00:13:53,067 --> 00:13:54,233
I just want
to congratulate Bobby

325
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,100
on saving Selena, right?

326
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:57,200
Hey.

327
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:58,800
You know, let's just pray

328
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:03,200
that Bobby's godsister
will be saved.

329
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:05,300
- Okay?
- Correct.

330
00:14:05,433 --> 00:14:07,033
- Let's go
- Oh, let's go.

331
00:14:08,967 --> 00:14:10,933
Sir, this is it, isn't it?

332
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:13,433
This is where they said
Cherry's pick-up point

333
00:14:13,567 --> 00:14:15,467
when she books a motorbike.

334
00:14:17,767 --> 00:14:18,900
You're right.

335
00:14:19,033 --> 00:14:20,200
This is it.

336
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:21,767
What's the plan, Sir Fred?

337
00:14:23,033 --> 00:14:24,167
Let's go around the vicinity.

338
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,500
Let's ask if anyone saw
Cherry yesterday.

339
00:14:27,633 --> 00:14:29,433
Because last night,
when Noble and I went around,

340
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:31,333
we wren't able to talk
to anyone.

341
00:14:33,433 --> 00:14:34,367
There they are.

342
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:41,267
What are you doing here?

343
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,633
Didn't I ask Noble to accompany
you both to the station

344
00:14:43,767 --> 00:14:45,300
to file a police report?

345
00:14:45,433 --> 00:14:48,100
Sir, we're done
with the police report.

346
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:52,067
We want to join
the search for our friend.

347
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,033
Who said you could come along?

348
00:14:54,167 --> 00:14:55,633
Oh, them.

349
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:59,100
Are you two serious?

350
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:02,533
We can't bring civilians with us
when we're investigating.

351
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,667
Well, Sir, they volunteered.

352
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:07,733
Oh, don't scold them, Sir Fred.

353
00:15:07,867 --> 00:15:10,167
We're the ones who volunteered
to come along,

354
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:13,833
so that we can search
for Cherry faster.

355
00:15:13,967 --> 00:15:15,133
And one more thing, Sir,

356
00:15:15,267 --> 00:15:18,333
we believe that your search
will be faster,

357
00:15:18,467 --> 00:15:22,500
if we're with you
because we know her well.

358
00:15:22,633 --> 00:15:24,967
Okay, then...

359
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:28,500
let's split up so that
our coverage will be broader.

360
00:15:28,633 --> 00:15:30,000
Let's regroup here.

361
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,833
That's right, it's your
obligation! That's your pet.

362
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,167
- What's happening?
- Oh, my!

363
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,633
- What?
- You're always like that!

364
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:39,933
- You complain so much!
- Why?

365
00:15:40,067 --> 00:15:42,433
Why? Is that my pet? Am I the
one who should take care of it?

366
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,667
Me? Am I the owner?

367
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:44,600
-No way!
-Report me to the village office

368
00:15:44,733 --> 00:15:45,633
if you have a complaint!

369
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:47,133
- Yes, I will!
- You really have a lot to say!

370
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:48,800
- Hey, hey, hey.
- Well, of course!

371
00:15:48,933 --> 00:15:49,867
What are you fighting about?

372
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:51,200
Captain, it's her fault.

373
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:55,867
Bernadette's dog always poops
in front of our house.

374
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,167
It's because your house smells
like a toilet.

375
00:15:58,300 --> 00:15:59,967
My dog always smells it!

376
00:16:00,100 --> 00:16:02,267
That's because your mouth
is close to your nose!

377
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,367
- Oh, enough!
- I don't know about you.

378
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,767
Miss...

379
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:08,167
maybe we can do something
about your dog.

380
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:11,300
That's it, I know my dog
is wrong.

381
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:13,933
I'm willing to clean it up
and throw it away properly.

382
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:16,367
But my neighbor...

383
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,200
threw it in our house!

384
00:16:18,333 --> 00:16:19,400
The dog?

385
00:16:19,533 --> 00:16:20,900
No, the poop!

386
00:16:21,033 --> 00:16:22,633
Why did you do that?

387
00:16:22,767 --> 00:16:24,533
Because I'm so fed up.

388
00:16:24,667 --> 00:16:26,400
It happens every day,
and it's not getting any better!

389
00:16:26,533 --> 00:16:27,500
The dog?

390
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:29,033
No, Bernadette!

391
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:30,767
If she can't control her dog,

392
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:33,233
she should lock it inside
the house so it can't come out!

393
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:36,167
But what you did
was still wrong.

394
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:37,033
I agree.

395
00:16:37,167 --> 00:16:38,867
You shouldn't have thrown
the poop

396
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,600
outside Bernadette's house
just to get revenge.

397
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:42,867
Wait, Captain.

398
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,333
What's the solution?

399
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:46,833
How do you properly
dispose of dog poop?

400
00:16:46,967 --> 00:16:48,133
It's simple.

401
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:49,800
Get a dustpan.

402
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:51,333
Get some soil,

403
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:52,767
then put it in the dustpan.

404
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:55,733
Then pick up the dog poop.

405
00:16:55,867 --> 00:16:59,067
Then cover the poop
with soil again.

406
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,900
Then find some trash bins.

407
00:17:02,033 --> 00:17:04,867
Captain, that's a great project.

408
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,067
Right!

409
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:10,900
So you, every morning,
go find some dog poop.

410
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:14,233
Get a dustpan
and do what I said.

411
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,467
You throw the dog poop
in the trash, okay?

412
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:18,800
That sounds nice.

413
00:17:18,933 --> 00:17:20,000
- Nice, right?
- Yes.

414
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:20,967
You deserve it.

415
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,633
And you, Mothers,

416
00:17:23,767 --> 00:17:25,867
please patch things up.

417
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,433
Don't let that fight drag on,
okay?

418
00:17:28,567 --> 00:17:30,967
Anyway, we have a new solution.

419
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:33,067
- Take care of your dog
- Yes, Captain. Sorry.

420
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:33,967
Sorry too, Captain.

421
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:35,400
Sis, sorry.

422
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:37,467
Oh, very good.

423
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:38,567
Love you, love you.

424
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,600
- Thank you very much.
- Okay, bye.

425
00:17:40,733 --> 00:17:41,967
- Thank you.
- Oh, let's go, Captain.

426
00:17:42,100 --> 00:17:43,133
Don't do that again.

427
00:17:43,267 --> 00:17:44,967
- Just love each other, okay?
- Yes.

428
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,267
- Isn't it fun?
- Next time, okay?

429
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:47,667
Next time, the trash...

430
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:51,067
<i>We'll continue with our mission
now, Grandmother. Wish us luck.</i>

431
00:17:51,233 --> 00:17:53,067
Aren't I like
a fairy godmother there?

432
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,700
Good luck to you, my grandchild.

433
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:57,133
May God guide you.

434
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:10,000
This is what I'm preparing for,

435
00:18:10,133 --> 00:18:13,167
to use my fighting skills
abroad.

436
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,000
Enriquez, it's not too late.

437
00:18:15,133 --> 00:18:16,667
If you want,
just watch over Selena.

438
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,767
Bok and I can handle this.

439
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:22,500
- Enriquez.
- Sir?

440
00:18:22,667 --> 00:18:23,733
Be careful, okay?

441
00:18:23,867 --> 00:18:25,133
Yes, Sir.

442
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:30,033
You two, just call me
when you need help, okay?

443
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:32,433
I'm the only one
who's good at this.

444
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:34,567
Maybe it's better
if we split up...

445
00:18:37,867 --> 00:18:40,533
You've already thought
of what I'm thinking.

446
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,833
What we're doing feels so good,
right?

447
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:50,567
Imagine, we've cleaned up
the street,

448
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:52,500
we've even helped the residents.

449
00:18:52,633 --> 00:18:54,000
That's right.

450
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,733
That's what real
service means, right?

451
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,100
Wait a minute...

452
00:18:58,233 --> 00:19:00,200
- What's this?
- An old woman is sleeping.

453
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,233
Wait, wait.

454
00:19:04,567 --> 00:19:05,533
Grandmother...

455
00:19:05,667 --> 00:19:07,167
Grandmother...

456
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:09,033
Oh, Grandmother...

457
00:19:09,167 --> 00:19:10,333
Oh, hello.

458
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:12,667
Oh, why?

459
00:19:12,800 --> 00:19:16,533
Grandmother, why are you
sleeping here?

460
00:19:16,667 --> 00:19:17,600
Don't you have anyone with you?

461
00:19:17,733 --> 00:19:19,067
Are you alone here?

462
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,467
Me.

463
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,833
Good evening, Captain.

464
00:19:21,967 --> 00:19:23,900
- Good evening.
- I'm with her.

465
00:19:24,033 --> 00:19:26,733
I just went out to get
some food, Captain,

466
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:29,533
because grandmother and I
haven't eaten for a few days.

467
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,233
Grandmother, let's eat.

468
00:19:31,367 --> 00:19:32,667
Captain, let's eat.

469
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:33,900
Sir, join us.

470
00:19:34,033 --> 00:19:35,233
Thank you.

471
00:19:35,367 --> 00:19:38,033
Oh my, sorry
for the inconvenience.

472
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:39,400
Oh, no, that's okay.

473
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:40,967
You're not bothering us.

474
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:44,200
And as guards here
in our village,

475
00:19:44,333 --> 00:19:47,767
it's our duty to look after you.

476
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:50,900
Grandmother,
how can we help you?

477
00:19:51,033 --> 00:19:54,700
Captain, our house
was damaged by the typhoon.

478
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:57,333
And some of our other
belongings, Captain...

479
00:19:57,467 --> 00:19:59,033
the got washed away
by the flood.

480
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:02,433
I hope you can give us
a place to stay.

481
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:06,567
Even if it's just temporarily,
Captain.

482
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:09,533
Okay, you can stay at the
village hall for now,

483
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:12,300
while we fix your house.

484
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:14,500
Really, Captain?

485
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:18,900
Oh my, thank you very much,
Captain.

486
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:20,167
Thank you, Captain.

487
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:22,500
Come on, let me help you fix
your belongings.

488
00:20:22,633 --> 00:20:23,633
- Okay, thank you.
- Okay, okay.

489
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,167
- Thank you, Captain.
- Thank you.

490
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:27,767
- Yes, Grandmother. Okay, okay.
- Captain, thank you.

491
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:30,033
Captain, aren't you coming?

492
00:20:30,167 --> 00:20:31,333
I'll go home first.

493
00:20:31,467 --> 00:20:33,067
I'll look for some food,

494
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:36,267
and I'll take it to the village
hall for them.

495
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,967
Captain, you're really kind.

496
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:41,733
I remember Bobby.

497
00:20:41,867 --> 00:20:44,433
Why? Did you live
on the sidewalk too?

498
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:47,400
If no one had helped us,

499
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:50,433
we'd probably still be
on the sidewalk by now.

500
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,667
Markus!

501
00:23:10,467 --> 00:23:12,067
Enriquez!

502
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:18,567
- Sir!
- Are you okay?

503
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,233
Yes, I'm okay, Sir!

504
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:22,367
Chase him! That's where he went,
hurry up!

505
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:37,767
You beast!

506
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,600
What are you doing
to my grandmother?

507
00:23:39,733 --> 00:23:41,767
I know you have Selena Madrigal.

508
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:43,200
Give her back to me,

509
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:45,433
or I'll blow
your grandmother's head off.

510
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:47,133
Don't hurt my grandmother, okay?

511
00:23:47,267 --> 00:23:50,567
If you want, just take me
instead of my grandmother!

512
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:52,367
I hope there's a miracle.

513
00:23:52,500 --> 00:23:54,167
I hope we can save
Grandmother Isang.

514
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:56,100
- What are you doing?
- I'm a majorette.

515
00:23:56,267 --> 00:23:57,867
I'm an electric fan.
How about you?

516
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:58,867
I'm rowing.

517
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:01,867
What?

518
00:24:03,100 --> 00:24:04,267
Boss, I'm just kidding!

519
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:09,533
One hour, otherwise,
your grandmother will be dead.

520
00:24:09,667 --> 00:24:11,367
Markus, I can't do that!

521
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:13,100
Well, take me to them.

